
[1]facing

   FA'CING, ppr. [from face.]

   1. Fronting; having the face towards; opposite.

   2. Covering the fore part.

   3. Turning the face.

   FA'CING, n. A covering in front for ornament or defense; as the facing
                     of a fortification or of a garment.
